The mother-of-one told KFOR-TV that she was sleeping heavily when the blaze broke out, but she was woken by True's barking.

She said: 'I thought he had to go outside. When I opened the door, it was a wall of flames.

'By the time I was out of the back door, all the windows had busted out and there were flames in every room.

'We lost everything, nothing is salvagable.'

