Katie said she grabbed Jace and ran through thick smoke to escape out the back of the property.

With the family safe, Katie's biggest sadness is losing the toys, belongings and photographs from Jace's first year, as well as his medical records and her mother's antiques.

She said: 'That’s the hardest part, having all that stuff from when he was little.'

But she has nothing but praise for True, the dog that rewarded her kindness by saving her and infant's life.

She said: 'We’re thankful for him. This could have been a bad deal.'

